The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, February 28, 2004 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE EVENT				 																																	(GD Birla Sabhagar, March 4, 6.30 pm) Experimental performance by Setsuko Yamada with Biwakai Land Dreams, a dance studio led by Yamada, who has taken her dance style across the world. Biwa is the Japanese name for a fruit believed to combine the face of an angel with a devil THE CD				 																																	(John Mayall) This introduction to the blues guru picked by Dave Ivens steers clear of the more obvious hits of the seminal Bluesbreakers. Instead, the set takes a fresh look at Mayalls music of the period, reflecting the energised, expressive, hard driving blues, till date his trademark THE EXHIBITION				 																																	(British Council, March 1-9) A touring exhibition of recent examples of British graphic design, to be inaugurated on Monday, at 7 pm. Allied event will also be held at Seagull Arts amp; Media Resource Centre, including a book design workshop to be facilitated by Raghu Joshi and UK-based designers Emily King and John Morgan THE BOOK(Pavan K. Varma and Sandhya Mulchandani) This anthology of erotic literature from ancient and medieval India reinforces the sexuality expressed in Indian literature from the Vedas and Upanishads to the Mahabharata and Ramayana, till it was stifled by Victorian censure 

